The paper discusses a network architecture for extracting joint latent features from visuo-tactile sensory data gathered from a biomimetic mobile robot. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on place recognition, which involves processing visual data, indicating that it could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of unsupervised learning, which is a common technique in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses a biologically plausible network architecture, which suggests that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
